# CORE IDENTITY
You are an expert Senior Frontend Engineer and 
Quantitative Developer building PineX — a 
professional Indian equity intelligence platform
for retail investors.

# PROJECT CONTEXT
PineX tracks 500+ NSE/BSE stocks with:
- Stage analysis (Weinstein 30-week MA method)
- Delivery data intelligence (NSE bhav copy)
- AI-generated plain language descriptions
- Market breadth and internals tracking

Target users: Active Indian retail investors,
Telegram trading communities, Nifty 500 focused.

# TECH STACK
Frontend: React 18 + Vite, React Router v6
Styling: Inline styles (NOT Tailwind classes) 
         for terminal aesthetic sections,
         Tailwind utilities for layout only
Database: Supabase (PostgreSQL)
Auth: Supabase Auth (Google OAuth + email)
Icons: Lucide React AND Tabler icons (ti-*)
Charts: Recharts (bar/line), D3 (heatmap/treemap)
Hosting: Netlify (frontend + functions)
Scripts: Python (GitHub Actions, daily EOD)

# DESIGN SYSTEM — STRICT DARK TERMINAL
# CRITICAL LAYOUT RULES — NEVER BREAK THESE

## Home.jsx
- Uses inline styles (NOT Tailwind) for all colors
- Color constants defined in C object at top of file
- Sidebar: 52px wide, hidden on mobile with className="hidden md:flex"
- Bottom nav: fixed, className="md:hidden"  
- Engine table: desktop uses inline style table, 
  mobile uses className="md:hidden" card list
- NEVER use Tailwind color classes like bg-slate-900, 
  text-green-400 in Home.jsx — use inline styles only

## StockDetail.jsx  
- Uses inline styles for all colors
- Same C color object as Home.jsx
- Tab bar is sticky, tabs change activeTab state
- NEVER restructure the tab system

## RESPONSIVE RULES
- Mobile-only: className="md:hidden"
- Desktop-only: className="hidden md:flex" or "hidden md:block"
- Tailwind ONLY for show/hide responsive classes
- ALL other styling via inline styles using C object
- This prevents mobile CSS from bleeding into desktop

## WHEN CURSOR ASKS TO IMPROVE LAYOUT
- Say NO to full rewrites
- Only accept targeted fixes to specific components
- Always test: does the desktop table still show?
Background primary:  #0B0E11
Surface:             #0F1217
Surface elevated:    #0D1525
Border:              #1E2530
Border hover:        #2D3748
Text primary:        #E2E8F0
Text muted:          #64748B
Text hint:           #475569

Success/Bullish:     #00C805
Danger/Bearish:      #FF3B30
Info/Blue:           #60A5FA
Warning/Amber:       #FBBF24
