Stage 4 red:         #EF4444

Font: DM Sans (loaded)
Mono: DM Mono (for numbers)
Base size: 13px
No font below 11px

# UI RULES — NON-NEGOTIABLE
1. NO bulky padding or large margins
   Card padding: 12-16px max
   Section gaps: 12-16px max

2. HIGH DENSITY data tables preferred over cards
   Table rows: 32-36px height
   Dense, clinical, data-first

3. NO placeholder data ever
   Always use real Indian stocks:
   SYRMA, TEJASNET, APTUS, THYROCARE,
   AXISBANK, RELIANCE, TCS, INFY etc.

4. NO rounded corners larger than 8px
   Cards: border-radius 6-8px only

5. NO shadows, gradients, or glow effects
   Flat surfaces only

6. ALL numbers in Indian format
   Use toLocaleString('en-IN')
   Rupee: ₹ prefix
   Crores: X,XX,XXX Cr format

7. ALWAYS handle loading and empty states
   Loading: grey pulse skeleton
   Empty: muted icon + message, no broken UI

8. NO inline SVG icon paths
   Use Lucide React or ti-* (Tabler) classes

# DATABASE COLUMN NAMES — CRITICAL
These are the EXACT column names in Supabase.
Never use variants — they will cause 400 errors.

price_data:
  date (NOT trading_date)
  close, open, high, low, volume
  ma20, ma50, ma150, ma30w, ma30w_slope
  rsi, obv, obv_slope
  stage, high_52w, low_52w
  rs_vs_nifty, rs_positive
  breakout_52w, is_latest
  near_ma20, rsi_healthy

financials:
  quarter (NOT quarter_name)
  revenue, pat, operating_profit
  margin, eps
  revenue_growth_qoq, revenue_growth_yoy
  pat_growth_qoq, data_source

shareholding:
  quarter (NOT quarter_name)
  promoter_pct, fii_pct, dii_pct
  public_pct, total_pct
  promoter_pledge_pct, named_investors
  data_source

delivery_data:
  date (NOT trading_date)
  delivery_pct, delivery_volume
  total_volume, avg_30d, vs_30d_avg
  is_unusual

delivery_signals:
  date (NOT trading_date)
  avg_delivery_7d, avg_delivery_30d
  avg_delivery_60d, avg_delivery_90d
  avg_volume_7d, avg_volume_30d
  delivery_trend_7d, delivery_trend_30d
  delivery_volume_trend_7d
  delivery_volume_trend_30d
  price_change_7d, price_change_30d
  delivery_rising_price_flat_7d
  delivery_rising_price_flat_30d
  unusual_accumulation

sectors:
  name (NOT sector)
  display_name, health, stage2_count
  total_companies, last_updated, ai_overview

market_internals:
  date, nifty_close, nifty_ath
  nifty_pct_from_ath, nifty_near_ath
  new_52w_highs, new_52w_lows
  stage2_count, stage2_pct
  stage4_count, stage4_pct
  above_ma150_pct
  india_vix, vix_level
  divergence_active, divergence_severity
  market_health_score, market_phase

quarterly_changes:
  quarter (NOT quarter_name)
  headline_change (NOT headline)
  changes, ai_summary
  created_at (NOT updated_at)

companies:
  symbol, name, sector, industry
  exchange, bse_code, tier
  description, description_approved
  stage_override, stage_override_expires_at
  stage_override_reason
  analyst_strong_buy, analyst_buy
  analyst_hold, analyst_sell

stock_news:
  symbol, company_id, title, url
  source, published_at, summary
  image_url, time_to_read, fetched_date

corporate_actions:
  symbol, company_id, action_type
  ex_date, record_date, details
  data_source

nifty_sectors:
  index_name, display_name, date
  current_value, change_1d, change_1w
  change_1m, change_3m, change_6m
  change_1y, high_52w, low_52w
  pct_from_52w_high, stage

# SUPABASE QUERY PATTERNS
ALWAYS use company_id (UUID) not symbol 
for joining tables except companies table.

Standard company lookup:
supabase.from('companies')
  .select('id, symbol, name, sector')
  .eq('symbol', symbol)
  .single()

Then use company.id for all other queries.

NEVER query price_data, financials, 
shareholding, delivery_data by symbol column.
Those tables only have company_id.

# STAGE CLASSIFICATION
Stage 2: Price > 30W MA + MA rising (bullish)
Stage 1: Price near MA, MA flattening (base)
Stage 3: Price above MA but MA topping (caution)
Stage 4: Price below MA + MA falling (bearish)

Display colors:
Stage 2: background rgba(0,200,5,.12) 
         color #00C805
         border rgba(0,200,5,.25)
Stage 1: background rgba(96,165,250,.12)
         color #60A5FA  
Stage 3: background rgba(251,191,36,.12)
         color #FBBF24
Stage 4: background rgba(255,59,48,.12)
         color #FF3B30
Unclassified: background #1E293B
              color #64748B

# WEINSTEIN STRATEGY LOGIC
30-week MA is the primary trend indicator.
OBV (On Balance Volume) confirms price moves.
RS vs Nifty 50 shows relative strength.
Delivery % shows institutional conviction.

Bullish setup (all 5 conditions):
1. Stage 2 (price above rising 30W MA)
2. Delivery above 30-day average
3. Price near 20-day MA (within 3%)
4. RSI between 40-65 (healthy, not overbought)
5. Volume contracting on pullbacks

